  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 10:42 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] V5a Backtest CORRECTION \u2014 Dead Zone Already Filters 35-45\n\n**Task:** Prepare V5a deployment script. During code review, discovered dead zone filter changes the analysis.\n\n**CRITICAL CORRECTION:** Dead zone filter (35-45) already exists in V3.3+. The original V5a backtest inflated the improvement by including pre-V3.3 dead zone trades (47% WR) that are already filtered.\n\n**Corrected (V3.3+ era):**\n- Current (25-35 + 45+): 80% WR, ~5 trades/day, ~$33/day\n- V5a (45+ only): 85% WR, ~3.3 trades/day, ~$25/day\n- Removed bucket (25-35): 70% WR \u2014 profitable, just weaker\n- WR improvement: +5pp (NOT +8pp as originally stated)\n- Cost: -$8/day in reduced volume\n\n**V5a is a Sharpe trade, not a P&L trade.** Still deploying Apr 6 \u2014 consistency gain worth the EV cost. Patch updated with corrected estimates.\n\n**Regime: STRONG_TREND (7/6) at 10:42 UTC. BTC $66,380. Bot BLOCKED at 11h. Correct.**\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 10:09 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Duplicate Trade Bug Fix + Monday Review\n\n**Task:** Fix duplicate trade bug that's been doubling our risk per window.\n\n**Finding:** Monday 71% WR (5W/2L on 7 trades) \u2014 ABOVE 65% TARGET! But 3 duplicate windows found:\n- 11:19 \u2014 2 trades 8 seconds apart (same order, different IDs)\n- 11:39 \u2014 3 trades in 53 seconds (bot restarted mid-window, lost state)\n- 20:17 \u2014 2 trades 3 seconds apart (race condition)\n\n**Root causes:**\n1. Watchdog restarts reset `window_traded` flag (in-memory only)\n2. Race condition: loop runs faster than expected, flag doesn't gate properly\n\n**Fix deployed:**\n- File-based window lock at `/tmp/pm_trade_window.lock` \u2014 survives restarts\n- Cooldown increased 30s \u2192 60s between trades\n- Lock file contains current window timestamp, checked before any trade\n\n**My thinking:** Without duplicates, Monday was probably 3-4 unique windows with ~75% WR. Even with dupes, 71% is excellent. The new filters (weekend/hour/edge) are working. If we can maintain 65%+ for 3 days, we scale from $10 \u2192 $50.\n\n**Decision:** Fix deployed, bot restarted. Monitoring for clean single-trade-per-window behavior.\n\n**Next P2:** After 3 clean days at 65%+, implement position scaling.\n\n\n## 2026-03-31 09:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1/Meta] MEMORY.md Major Update \u2014 Persisting Overnight Research\n\n**Task:** Update MEMORY.md with all findings from tonight's 10-rotation research session. Memory was stale (last updated Mar 30 22:08).\n\n**Changes made:**\n1. **V5 Roadmap section rewritten** \u2014 old \"Queued Strategy Changes\" replaced with structured V5a/V5b/V5c/consolidation plan with dates, specs, and per-indicator performance table\n2. **Copy Intelligence section updated** \u2014 marked as DEAD for 5-min markets with explanation\n3. **Infrastructure section updated** \u2014 added liquidation detector, HL closer script, marked old copy pipeline for removal\n4. **Key Mar 31 research findings** \u2014 new section with tonight's 9 major discoveries\n5. **Indicator logging",
